President Biden delivered a speech at the Marriott Marquis in Chicago, thanking supporters and discussing his administration's accomplishments and goals. He expressed gratitude to Governor Pritzker and others for their support during his campaign and highlighted the progress made in areas such as COVID-19 vaccinations, job creation, deficit reduction, and infrastructure investments. He emphasized the need to address the challenges facing democracy and the importance of unity and consensus in a changing world. The President also discussed the radical agenda of some Republicans and the potential consequences of their policies, including threats to women's rights, civil rights, and social programs. He urged supporters to stay engaged and work towards maintaining Democratic control of Congress in order to protect and advance their values.